Sentencas: Nd1.95NiO4+delta (NNO) cathode supported microtubular cells were fabricated and characterized.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This material presents superior oxygen transport properties in comparison with other commonly used cathode materials.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The supporting tubes were fabricated by cold isostatic pressing (CIP) using NNO powders and corn starch as pore former.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrolyte (GDC, gadolinia doped ceria based) was deposited by wet powder spraying (WPS) on top of pre-sintered tubes and then co-sintered.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Finally, a NiO/GDC suspension was dip-coated and sintered as the anode.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Optimization of the cell fabrication process is shown.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Power densities at 750 degrees C of similar to 40 mWcm(-2) at 0.5V were achieved.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results are the first electrochemical measurements reported using NNO cathode-supported microtubular cells.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Further developments of the fabrication process are needed for this type of cells in order to compete with the standard microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.95NiO4+δ Cathode supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
